Title: gccMurmurHash
Description: Calculates a 64-bit MurmurHash2 hash value using the same hash seed as gcc. It is portable between Clang and GCC builds.
par1, ... — A variable number of parameters that can be any of the supported data types.
Examples: SELECT    gccMurmurHash(1, 2, 3) AS res1,    gccMurmurHash(('a', [1, 2, 3], 4, (4, ['foo', 'bar'], 1, (1, 2)))) AS res2
